      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In Node.js, JavaScript objects including arrays, have a concept called \"closure\" where references to global variables capture the value of a global variable at the time the scope was defined. When you append to an array using `push()`, a new reference is created, but every iteration of the `for` loop retains the reference to the entire array from the previous iteration, increasing the memory usage over time. This can cause a memory leak.",
