      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When you terminate a cluster in Node.js, all insistors (child processes) associated with the worker process are terminated, but it may not automatically clean up other linked child processes in the background. To ensure all linked child processes are properly cleaned up, ensure that the `worker_files` option is set to an empty array, and both `maxDominaticFiles` and `maxIdleRequests` are set to 0 in your cluster configuration.",
